  "prompt": "How do deaf people communicate?",
  "response": "Deaf people communicate through various methods, including:\n\n1. Sign Language\n- American Sign Language (ASL)\n- British Sign Language (BSL)\n- Other regional sign languages\n- Uses hand gestures, facial expressions, and body language\n\n2. Visual Communication Methods\n- Lip reading\n- Writing\n- Texting\n- Typing\n- Drawing\n- Gestures\n\n3. Assistive Technologies\n- Hearing aids\n- Cochlear implants\n- Text telephones (TTY)\n- Video relay services\n- Captioning\n- Speech-to-text apps\n\n4. Non-Manual Communication\n- Facial expressions\n- Body language\n- Pointing\n- Pantomime\n\n5. Fingerspelling\n- Spelling out words letter by letter using hand shapes\n- Used for names, technical terms, or words without a specific sign\n\n6. Oral Communication\n- Some deaf individuals learn to speak and read lips\n- Can use speech therapy techniques\n\nThe communication method varies depending on individual preference, hearing loss level, cultural background, and personal comfort.",
